dark.objects is a library for working with objects.

  `Na`(`Vx`, `Vy`, `Vz`): `Napplies` `Vz` to `Vx`[`Vy`]
  `Nb`:          (not yet used)
  `Nc`(...`Vx`):    `Nclones` entries from `Vx` into new object
  `Nd`(`Vx`, `Vy`, `Vz`): `Ndefaults` `Vx`[`Vy`] to `Vz`(), returning value
  `Ne`(`Vx`):       makes array of `Nentries` in `Vx` (*)
  `Nf`(`Vx`, `Vy`):    maps `Nfirst` values in `Vx` by keys `Vy`
  `Ng`(`Vx`, `Vy`):    `Ngets` `Vx`[`Vy`] if `Vy` is text, or calls `Vy`(`Vx`)
  `Nh`(`Vx`, ...`Vy`): checks if `Vx` `Nhas` the properties `Vy`
  `Ni`:          (not yet used)
  `Nj`(`Vx`):       converts from JSON string
  `Nk`(`Vx`):       makes array of `Nkeys` in `Vx`
  `Nl`(`Vx`, `Vy`):    makes `Nlists` of values in `Vx` with keys `Vy`
  `Nm`(`Vx`):       `Nmakes` object from array of entries
  `Nn`:          (not yet used)
  `No`:          (not yet used)
  `Np`:          (not yet used)
  `Nq`:          (not yet used)
  `Nr`:          (not yet used)
  `Ns`(`Vx`, ...`Vy`): `Nsets` entries in `Vx` using entries from `Vy`
  `Nt`(`Vx`):       `Ntext` key for object, with keys in order
  `Nu`(`Vx`):       `Nunwraps` array values in `Vx` into cross product
  `Nv`(`Vx`):       makes array of defined `Nvalues` in `Vx`
  `Nw`:          (not yet used)
  `Nx`:          (not yet used)
  `Ny`:          (not yet used)
  `Nz`:          (not yet used)
  `N$`(`Vx`):       makes `Nshortcut` object from `Vx` using concatenation of keys
  `N_`:          (not yet used)
